On 2 Feb 1999, Kirk Reiser wrote:
> Hello Everyone: I was wondering if anyone else has noticed that
> sometimes the ppp0 and other ppp interfaces are not getting dropped
> when the modem disconnects under the newer kernels.  Actually, this
> box is running 2.1.131, so I can't really speak for versions more
> current than that.
> 
> If I take the interface down with ifconfig, it comes back up just fine
> the next time.  I have not been able to determine an actual event
> which causes the problem though.
> 
There is now a script in /etc/ppp that is used to make networking
changes when the link comes up or goes down. (/etc/ppp/ip_up,
/etc/ppp/ip_down). You put whatever you need in there.
Cheers,
Dick Johnson
